Description

Represents an account that all Employees (Staff, Manager, Admin) Employee has, to log in to the system.

This is the main class of the application.
Branch
Represents a branch of the restaurant.
Customer
Represents a customer of the restaurant A customer can make an order, check the status of their order, pay for their order and collect their order.

Class for reading and writing from/to files

An abstract class representing an Employee.

This class represents a Food object on the menu
IActionable
An interface representing objects that can perform certain actions.
IPayable
An interface to represent the payment implementation when customers pay for their orders.
Logger
This class provides functionality for logging messages, verbose mode will be made active once App runs, allowing messages to be printed.
Manager
This class represents a Manager of the restaurant, extending from the Staff class since a manager can do what a Staff can do but more (such as modifying menu)
Menu
Menu class represents the menu of a branch, with functionality such as adding/removing food to/from a menu, updating price/availability of a food item, and displaying a menu.
Order
This class represents an Order, made by a Customer.
Order.OrderStatus
Enum representing the status of an Order.
PayCash
PayCash class simulates payment by a customer using cash.
PayDebit
PayDebit class simulates payment by a customer using a debit card.
PayMethod
Class representing payment method.
PayMobile
PayMobile class simulates payment by a customer using a mobile method.

PayNETS class simulates payment by a customer using a NETS method.
